With a focus on alignment and stability, Teresa approaches yoga with mindfulness and self-compassion, allowing her practice to evolve and meet her where she is each day.

After spending twenty years as a stay-at-home mom, Teresa felt called to deepen her personal journey by enrolling in a 200-hour yoga teacher training. Initially, she had no intention of teaching and simply wanted to learn more about herself and her practice. However, upon completing the training, she realized that becoming a yoga teacher was the natural next step on her path.

Teresa received her 200-hour certification from Hot Asana Yoga University in Southern Pines, North Carolina, and completed her 500-hour certification through Hot Asana in 2022. Her training includes specialized certifications in Yin Yoga, LSD (Long, Slow Deep), Hot Holds, and Reiki, through which she has become a Reiki Master.

Today, Teresa serves as the HOM (Head Operations Mamma) and Studio Manager at Love More, where she teaches classes, co-teaches Love More University’s 200-hour Yoga Teacher Training program and also offers Reiki sessions at the studio.  She also leads a Yin Yoga teacher training through Hot Asana Yoga University, sharing her passion for slow, intentional practice and helping others deepen their understanding of both yoga and themselves.`,
    socialLink: null,
