    bio: `I was born and raised in the Midwest. Sweet home Chicago! I grew up as an elite soccer and basketball player as well as an avid runner. For college, I ventured to Louisiana playing my way all the way to Louisiana Tech University where I met my best friend and husband of 10 years, Richard. In my 15 years of living in Louisiana, I became the mom to an amazing set of 9 year triplets James, Wyatt and Kathryn and our caboose, six year old, Grayson.

I tried my first hot yoga class twelve years ago and my passion was ignited. Now along with running on the trails, I can be found on my yoga mat or playing soccer with our four active kids. I recently obtained my 200hr RYT certification in 2018 to dive deeper into my own practice and share my love for yoga with others.  I have always loved kids and after having kids of my own, I realized that I wanted to make an impact in kids' learning by jumping into the teaching world. I am very passionate about growing minds of all ages, creating a safe and welcoming environment for kids to grow and learn. I also obtained my certification to teach kids yoga as well through Kids Yoga & Mindfulness at Love More Yoga in 2019.

