    title: "DPT, 200HR RYT",
    image: getTeamImage("../assets/images/team/kelsey-devries.jpg"),
    bio: `Kelsea DeVries is a native Coloradoan, but military spouse most recently moved to the Northshore from the Washington, DC area. She is a Doctor of Physical Therapy and a 200 hr RYT. She has 18 years experience in the physical therapy field, 5 years of teaching, and over 15 years yoga practice. Kelsea teaches from a place of wanting everyone to see their potential and encouraging students to go for it. Her classes are energetic and fun, possibly challenging at times, but always with modifications and the ability to meet students where they are at the present moment. Her playlists are often an eclectic mix of music ranging from oldies to new pop with pretty much anything in between. She also enjoys running, strength training, and Pilates. When not teaching or working out, Kelsea can be found exploring her new surroundings in Louisiana, enjoying time with her husband and two kids (8 and 11), playing with her new puppy, spending time outdoors, and traveling. 
`,
